Schnitzer Steel Industries, Inc. Key Developments

Schnitzer Steel Industries, Inc. Announces Unaudited Consolidated Earnings Results for the Third Quarter and Nine Months Ended May 31, 2017; Provides Earnings Guidance for the Year 2017
Jun 26 17
Schnitzer Steel Industries, Inc. announced unaudited consolidated earnings results for the third quarter and nine months ended May 31, 2017. For the quarter, the company’s total revenues were $477.088 million against $351.604 million a year ago. Operating income was $19.147 million against $14.886 million a year ago. Income from continuing operations before tax was $17.540 million against $11.900 million a year ago. Income from continuing operations was $17.379 million or $0.60 per diluted share against $11.805 million or $0.41 per diluted share a year ago. Net income attributable to the company was $16.565 million or $0.60 per diluted share against $11.000 million or $0.40 per diluted share a year ago. Adjusted net income from continuing operations attributable to company was $16 million or $0.56 per diluted share against loss of $13 million or $0.46 per diluted share a year ago. Adjusted operating income was $18 million against $15 million a year ago. Positive operating cash flow was $45 million reflecting improved profitability and benefits from lower working capital. Total debt at the end of the third quarter was $184 million.

For the nine months, the company’s total revenues were was $1,193.333 million against $961.880 million a year ago. Operating income was $33.905 million against loss of $26.217 million a year ago. Income from continuing operations before tax was $29.254 million against loss of $32.233 million a year ago. Income from continuing operations was $28.518 million or $0.96 per diluted share against loss of $33.043 million or $1.26 per diluted share a year ago. Net income attributable to the company was $26.276 million or $0.95 per diluted share against loss of $35.543 million or $1.31 per diluted share a year ago. Adjusted net income from continuing operations attributable to company was $25 million or $0.90 per diluted share against $2 million or $0.08 per diluted share a year ago. Adjusted operating income was $32 million against $9 million a year ago. 

The effective tax rate from continuing operations for fiscal 2017 is expected to be approximately 3%, subject to financial performance for the remainder of the year.


Schnitzer Steel Industries, Inc. Provides Preliminary Earnings Guidance for the Third Quarter Ended May 31, 2017
Jun 15 17
Schnitzer Steel Industries, Inc. provided preliminary earnings guidance for the third quarter ended May 31, 2017. The company expects third quarter earnings per share from continuing operations to be in the range of $0.56 - $0.60 and adjusted earnings per share to be in the range of $0.52 - $0.56. These expected results would reflect a significant increase compared to fiscal 2017 second quarter earnings per share of $0.40 and adjusted earnings per share of $0.37, and the prior year third quarter earnings per share of $0.41 and adjusted earnings per share of $0.46. Operating cash flow is expected to be in the range of $40 - $45 million. Total debt was $184 million as of the end of the third quarter which is a reduction of $25 million, or 12%, from the second quarter.


Schnitzer Steel Industries, Inc. to Report Q3, 2017 Results on Jun 26, 2017
Jun 15 17
Schnitzer Steel Industries, Inc. announced that they will report Q3, 2017 results at 11:30 AM, US Eastern Standard Time on Jun 26, 2017


