IT Budget




Schnitzer Steel Industries, Inc. provides of used and recycled auto parts and is manufacturer of finished steel products. The metals recycling division collects, processes, and recycles metal. The used auto parts division provides parts to customers across the US and… MoreSchnitzer Steel Industries, Inc. provides of used and recycled auto parts and is manufacturer of finished steel products. The metals recycling division collects, processes, and recycles metal. The used auto parts division provides parts to customers across the US and Canada. The steel manufacturing division transforms recycled scrap metal into quality finished steel products. Pick-n-Pull is a Schnitzer Steel subsidiary that recycles original equipment manufacturer (OEM) parts. Cascade Steel Rolling Mills is a subsidiary that manufactures steel products such as reinforcing bar (rebar), coiled reinforcing bar, wire rod, and merchant bar.
IT Struture
•The IT department at Schnitzer Steel Industries, Inc. handles technology for all three of the company's business units: Metals Recycling, Auto Parts, and Steel Manufacturing. 
•All three business units operate across the country at more than 100 locations, but… MoreIT Struture
•The IT department at Schnitzer Steel Industries, Inc. handles technology for all three of the company's business units: Metals Recycling, Auto Parts, and Steel Manufacturing. 
•All three business units operate across the country at more than 100 locations, but the vast majority of IT operations occur at the company's headquarters in Portland, Oregon.
 •IT for a subsidiary, Pick-N-Pull, is covered primarily by headquarters in Oregon, but also by an office in California. There is a Director of IT for Schnitzer Southeast's numerous locations in Alabama, Georgia, Tennessee, and Florida.





